items.title: India Inc eyes best earnings growth in 2 years, but 9 companies may see over 50% profit fall in Q3
items.description: India Inc anticipates its strongest earnings growth in two years. However, several companies are expected to face significant profit declines. IndusInd Bank, PI Industries, Welspun Living, GAIL India, NATCO Pharma, Orchid Pharma, Bajaj Electricals, Sapphire Foods India, and KNR Construction are projected to see profits drop by 50% or more.

items.title: Nifty 50 cos likely to see single-digit revenue and profit growth in December quarter
items.description: Nifty 50 companies are projected to see single-digit year-on-year growth in revenue and net profit for the December quarter. Analysts anticipate a recovery driven by policy support and domestic demand, with operating margins expected to remain above 20% for the 13th consecutive quarter.
